* INSTALL
Them you must patch mysql. Change directory into the mysql base directory which you extracted from tar-ball.
$ patch -p1 < mysql-5.1.28-29.patch

Make install the mysqld.

Compile the plugin
$ configure --with-mysql-config=/path/to/mysql_config
$ make
# make install

** From the repository
If you check out the source from the repository, you need autoconf, automake and libtool 
to build the plugin. Type as following:
$ aclocal
$ libtoolize --automake
$ automake --add-missing
$ automake
$ autoconf

Then you start a normal installation process.
$ ./configure --with-mysql-config=/path/to/mysql_config
$ make
# make install

